\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b1 Introduction}
\par\plain {4: Introductory paragraph clearly states subject of essay and captures reader's attention. }
\par\plain {3: Introductory paragraph states subject of essay but is not particularly inviting to the reader.}
\par\plain {2: Introductory paragraph attempts to state subject of essay but does not capture reader's attention.}
\par\plain {1: No attempt is made to state the subject of the essay in an introductory paragraph.}
\par\plain 
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1 Sensory Details}
\par\plain {4: Essay includes details that appeal to at least three of the five senses (taste, touch, sound, sight, smell).}
\par\plain {3: Includes details that appeal to fewer than three of the five senses.}
\par\plain {2: Includes details that appeal to only one of the five senses.}
\par\plain {1: Includes no details that appeal to one of the five senses.}
\par\plain 
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1 Word Choice}
\par\plain {4: Writer uses vivid words and phrases that linger or draw pictures in the reader's mind, and the choice and placement of the words seems accurate, natural and not forced.}
\par\plain {3: Writer uses vivid words and phrases that linger or draw pictures in the reader's mind, but occasionally the words are used inaccurately or seem overdone.}
\par\plain {2: Writer uses words that communicate clearly, but the writing lacks variety, punch or flair.}
\par\plain {1: Writer uses a limited vocabulary that does not communicate strongly or capture the reader's interest. Jargon or cliches may be present and detract from the meaning.}
\par\plain 
\par\plain {S}{\f0\fs24\b1 imile/Metaphor/Personification}
\par\plain {4: Writer effectively uses simile, metaphor, and personification to describe the subject.}
\par\plain {3: Writer uses one example of simile, metaphor, or personification to describe the subject.}
\par\plain {2: Writer may try to use simile, metaphor, and personification but does so incorrectly.}
\par\plain {1: Writer does not include simile, metaphor, or personification in essay.}
\par\plain 
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1 Sentence Structure (Sentence Fluency)}
\par\plain {4: All sentences are well-constructed with varied structure.}
\par\plain {3: Most sentences are well-constructed with varied structure.}
\par\plain {2: Most sentences are well-constructed but have a similar structure.}
\par\plain {1: Sentences lack structure and appear incomplete or rambling.}
